To calculate the Gross Profit Margin, we use the formula:

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = \left( \frac{\text{Gross Profit}}{\text{Total Revenue}} \right) \times 100 \]

From the given problem:
- Gross Profit = 279,378.77
- Total Revenue = 775,598.77

Now, plug these values into the formula:

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = \left( \frac{279,378.77}{775,598.77} \right) \times 100 \]

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} \approx 36.02\% \]

So, the solution is:

```json
{"solution": {'Gross Profit Margin': '36.02%'} }
```
